      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Implementing broad weight adjustments risks decreasing the model's sensitivity to subtle indicators clustered within specific high-risk behavioral profiles. The primary risk is inducing significant intelligence gaps by over-smoothing patterns that, while demographic, are indicative of higher risk factors in other dimensions. I must clarify that the trade-off isn't binary; we aim to refine the *basis* of the flags, not simply erase them. A targeted recalibration, rather than a blanket normalization, offers the best chance to maintain detection capability while addressing bias.",
